  "prompt": "Can you privately change your legal name so that it will not be public record?",
  "response": "In most jurisdictions, legally changing your name is a public process that involves filing court documents, which become part of the public record. There's typically no way to completely prevent the name change from being publicly accessible. However, in some rare cases, such as for victims of domestic violence or those facing safety concerns, a court may seal or restrict access to name change records. Generally, though, name changes are matters of public record.",
